> Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Chipotle Beef and Chorizo Rigatoni in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and @diced chorizo{90%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) to the beef. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir through the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @beef stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the cooked pasta and three quarters of the grated cheese.

Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

When ready, share your chipotle beef rigatoni between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese to finish. Enjoy!